### Content-Behind Curtain Model

The Ganesha content (icon, shlok, divider, button) is rendered BEHIND the curtain from page load. The curtain is a full-viewport overlay at higher z-index. When the curtain parts, it naturally uncovers the content underneath — no separate fade-in needed. This creates the authentic feeling of a real curtain being drawn open.

**Technical Implementation:**

- Content layer: `z-index: 1`, fully rendered, opacity: 1, positioned normally
- Curtain layer: `z-index: 50`, two absolutely positioned panels covering 100% viewport
- On page load: 0.5s pause, then both curtain panels translate outward (left panel: `translateX(-100%)`, right panel: `translateX(100%)`)
- Content is visible through the widening gap as curtains part
- After curtain fully opens: curtain panels removed from DOM (or `display: none`)
- Shlok lines animate AFTER curtain is fully open: line-by-line fade-in (0.3s stagger)
- Begin button fades in AFTER shlok completes

