## PALACE DOOR TRANSITION (Section 0 → Section 1)

When guest clicks "Begin", the Ganesha content fades out (0.3s) and ornate golden Rajasthani palace doors APPEAR over the screen, then swing open to reveal Section 1 content already waiting behind them.

### Content-Behind Door Model

Section 1 content is pre-rendered BEHIND the door layer. As doors swing outward, guests see the Opening Screen content through the widening gap between the doors. Content does NOT animate or fade in separately — it is simply revealed.

**Technical Implementation:**

- Step 1: Ganesha content fades out (0.3s)
- Step 2: Door overlay appears (z-index: 40) — two golden door panels covering viewport
- Step 3: Section 1 content renders behind doors (z-index: 1)
- Step 4: Doors swing outward using 3D `perspective(1200px)` + `rotateY` — left: `rotateY(-110deg)`, right: `rotateY(110deg)`
- Step 5: Golden radial light pours from center gap as doors open
- Step 6: 8-12 marigold petals drift from top of door frame
- Step 7: Doors reach full open → removed from DOM
- Section 1 content is now fully visible, static, ready for interaction

### Palace Door Design

| Property | Value |
| --- | --- |
| Door Panels | `#1A2A4A` base with `#C9A96E` jaali pattern overlay at 15% |
| Door Frame | `#C9A96E` solid gold, arch-topped |
| Jaali Pattern | SVG carved geometric pattern on each door panel |
| Brass Knockers | Ring handles on each door — CSS/SVG, antique gold |
| Animation | 3D `perspective(1200px)`  • `rotateY`. `transform-origin: left center` and `right center` |
| Duration | 1.8s (0.3s pause then 1.5s swing) |
| Easing | `cubic-bezier(0.22, 0.61, 0.36, 1)` — heavy doors feel |
| Light Effect | Golden radial gradient from center gap, expanding as doors open |
| Marigold Petals | 8-12 petals drift from top of frame during opening |
| Mobile Fallback | Fade-through-golden-light (no 3D perspective on low-end devices) |

